      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/27/17",
      "text": [
        " : \"اَلْبَعِيرُ بِالْبَعِيرَيْنِ وَ اَلدَّابَّةُ بِالدَّابَّتَيْنِ يَداً بِيَدٍ لَيْسَ بِهِ بَأْسٌ\" وَ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِالثَّوْبِ بِالثَّوْبَيْنِ يَداً بِيَدٍ وَ نَسِيئَةً إِذَا وَصَفْتَهُمَا \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4007 - Jamil ibn Darraj narrated from Zurarah, from Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), who said: \"There is no harm in exchanging a camel for two camels or an animal for two animals, as long as it is done hand-to-hand.\"\nAnd Imam (as) said: \"There is no harm in exchanging one garment for two garments, whether hand-to-hand or on credit, if you describe them.\""
        ]
      }
    },
